TITLE: Woman captured in alleged plot to assassinate Ukraine’s Zelenskyy
SUMMARY: Ukraine intelligence says a Russian informant was captured while trying to carry out a plot to assassinate President Zelenskyy during a trip to Mykolaiv last month. Meanwhile, a patrol of 11 Chinese and Russian warships cruised together near Alaska. NBC News’ Richard Engel has more details

TITLE: Deadly Russian missile strikes destroy hotel and apartments, Ukraine says
SUMMARY: Two missiles hit the center of Pokrovsk within 40 minutes of each other, witnesses said

TITLE: South Korea begins evacuating thousands of global Scouts from its coast as a tropical storm nears
SUMMARY: Tropical Storm Khanun has meandered around Japan’s southwestern islands for more than a week, dumping heavy rain, knocking out power and damaging homes

TITLE: Mourners gather in Ireland to say goodbye to Sinead O'Connor
SUMMARY: O’Connor was found unresponsive at her London home on July 26. Police have not said how she died, though they said her death was not suspicious. She was 56

TITLE: Italian man crushed to death by falling wheels of cheese
SUMMARY: Giacomo Chiapparini, 74, died in his warehouse near the city of Bergamo on Sunday evening

TITLE: Even frozen Antarctica is being walloped by climate extremes, scientists find
SUMMARY: One western glacier is melting so fast that scientists have nicknamed it the Doomsday Glacier and there’s an international effort trying to figure out what’s happening to it

TITLE: Eight Amazon rainforest countries begin first summit in 14 years
SUMMARY: Brazil’s environment and climate change minister said they aim to address how countries will prevent the Amazon's tipping point to start releasing carbon dioxide out of control

TITLE: Pope says Church open to everyone, including gay people, but has rules
SUMMARY: Since the start of his papacy, Francis has been trying to make the Church more welcoming and less condemning, including to members of the LGBTQ community

TITLE: Survivors of Mexican migrant detention center fire feel stuck and unable to support families
SUMMARY: Mexican immigration officials face criminal charges, including negligence and homicide, in a March fire that killed 40 people

TITLE: July was so hot that scientists think it has already been the hottest month ever
SUMMARY: The announcement from the World Meteorological Organization came the same day that President Joe Biden took steps intended to protect workers from extreme heat
